{"ALG_DESC": "This function identifies the component to which each edge belongs for the input line layer. This function first converts the input line layer into network data using the build3DNET function, and it is then converted to igraph using the GISigraph function to identify the component of edges. Please be cautious that the output layer is an exploded version of the line, meaning each line segment only has two connected vertices.", "line": "A 3D line layer", "filter":"A number indicating the component index within which the line segments are to be retained.  Default is -999, which indicates that no filtering is performed.", "lineComp":"A 3D line layer with an additional field called component, denoting the component for each line segment"}